text.__SUMMARY__: Saurauia latibractea is a species of plant in the family Annonaceae. It is native to The Philippines.  Jacques Denys Choisy, the Swill botanist who first formally described the species, named it after its broad (latus in Latin) bracts.  In Maranao it is called maragaoaq or tamiagau.
text.Description: It is a tree with oval or elliptical leaves that come to a point at their tip.  Its leaf margins are serrate.  Its flowers are axillary.  Its sepals are white.
text.Description-Reproductive biology: The pollen of S. elegans is shed as permanent tetrads.
